      "content": "but that's the thing, even the people I know feel like part of the fog. talking to them just feels like trying to scream underwater. everything is so heavy and loud and then there's this cliff... it's so quiet there. it's like the silence is calling me, telling me that the journey is finally over and I don't have to carry all this weight anymore. doesn't it just seem more poetic to let the story end where it's supposed to, rather than forcing it to go on into nothingness?",
